<Link id="l00067" /><CodeLine lineNumber="67"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00068" /><CodeLine lineNumber="68"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// A globally hashed type represents a hash value that is sufficient to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00069" /><CodeLine lineNumber="69"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// uniquely identify a record across multiple type streams or type sequences.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00070" /><CodeLine lineNumber="70"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// This works by, for any given record A which references B, replacing the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00071" /><CodeLine lineNumber="71"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// TypeIndex that refers to B with a previously-computed global hash for B.  As</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00072" /><CodeLine lineNumber="72"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// this is a recursive algorithm (e.g. the global hash of B also depends on the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00073" /><CodeLine lineNumber="73"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// global hashes of the types that B refers to), a global hash can uniquely</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00074" /><CodeLine lineNumber="74"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// identify that A occurs in another stream that has a completely</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00075" /><CodeLine lineNumber="75"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// different graph structure.  Although the hash itself is slower to compute,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00076" /><CodeLine lineNumber="76"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// probing is much faster with a globally hashed type, because the hash itself</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// is considered &quot;as good as&quot; the original type.  Since type records can be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="78"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// quite large, this makes the equality comparison of the hash much faster than</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="79"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// equality comparison of a full record.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="80" lineLink="/docs/api/structs/llvm/codeview/globallyhashedtype"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">struct </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/codeview/globallyhashedtype/#a9d71869a4b3222d94a767d6acaf44bfb">GloballyHashedType</a> &#123;</span></CodeLine>
